<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB01151</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT CREATING THE DEPARTMENT OF DISASTER RESILIENCE, DEFINING ITS POWER AND FUNCTIONS, APPROPRIATING FUNDS THEREFOR, AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Proposes to create a truly empowered department that will focus on natural hazards and disasters, characterized by unity of command, a science-and ICT-based approach, and the capacity to take charge of three (3) key result areas: 1) disaster risk reduction; 2) disaster preparedness and response; and 3) recovery, rehabilitation, etc.

Provides for key elements and features of the proposed Department as follows: a) unity of command, abolishing the Climate Change Commission and the NDRRMC; b) full-time focus on resilience to natural hazards; c) temporary take-over or direct any private utility for urgent public purpose; d) rationalized judicious and expeditious use of funds to help ensure the timely support where urgently and critically needed; e) innovative and responsive procurement mechanisms; f) Science and ICT-based approach to ensure real time access to relevant information; g) highly specialized functions and highly-skilled personnel requirements; h) institutional partnerships with LGUs, NGOs, and academia.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ROMUALDEZ, YEDDA MARIE K., ROMUALDEZ, FERDINAND MARTIN G.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-07-02</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Biazon (000 2019-09-03)</td><td>2. De Venecia (000 2019-09-17)</td><tr><td>3. Alonte (000 2020-01-27)</td><td>4. Geron (000 2020-01-28)</td><tr><td>5. Abueg-Zaldivar (000 2020-02-11)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>MOTHER BILL:&nbspHB05989</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON GOVERNMENT REORGANIZATION ON 2019-07-24</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SECONDARILY REFERRED TO THE COMMITTEE(S) ON DISASTER MANAGEMENT</td></tr></table>